abstract: All seven Democratic presidential candidates who qualified for next week's debate threatened on Friday to skip the event if an ongoing labor dispute forces them to cross picket lines on the campus hosting it.
snippet: All seven Democratic presidential candidates who qualified for next week's debate threatened on Friday to skip the event if an ongoing labor dispute forces them to cross picket lines on the campus hosting it.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — All seven Democratic presidential candidates who qualified for next week's debate threatened on Friday to skip the event if an ongoing labor dispute forces them to cross picket lines on the campus hosting it.
headline_main: Democrats Threaten to Boycott Next Debate Over Labor Dispute
headline_print_headline: Democrats Threaten to Boycott Next Debate Over Labor Dispute

abstract: ‘Trump anxiety disorder’ has morphed into anxiety about everything, and impeachment isn’t helping.
snippet: ‘Trump anxiety disorder’ has morphed into anxiety about everything, and impeachment isn’t helping.
lead_paragraph: GREENWOOD, S.C. — The past three years have not been easy for the political fortunes or the emotional health of America’s Democrats. To the extent they feel optimistic about anything, they have been waiting for the 2020 election in the way inhabitants of a storm-ravaged city might look toward the end of hurricane season — as an opportunity to restore order not just to their fractured physical world, but to their battered psyches.

abstract: Democratic presidential candidate Joe Biden gained two more endorsements from onetime backers of rival Kamala Harris' campaign, a sign of early strength in consolidating support after the U.S. senator left the race.
snippet: Democratic presidential candidate Joe Biden gained two more endorsements from onetime backers of rival Kamala Harris' campaign, a sign of early strength in consolidating support after the U.S. senator left the race.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Democratic presidential candidate Joe Biden gained two more endorsements from onetime backers of rival Kamala Harris' campaign, a sign of early strength in consolidating support after the U.S. senator left the race.
headline_main: Biden Lands Early Slate of Former Backers of Harris' Presidential Bid
headline_print_headline: Biden Lands Early Slate of Former Backers of Harris' Presidential Bid

abstract: The Democratic National Committee announced the next set of primary debates. One will be held in each of the early-voting states.
snippet: The Democratic National Committee announced the next set of primary debates. One will be held in each of the early-voting states.
lead_paragraph: Democratic presidential candidates will debate four times in January and February as the party’s opening quartet of nominating contests approaches, the Democratic National Committee said Thursday.

abstract: Businessman Andrew Yang qualified Tuesday to participate in next week's Democratic presidential debate, making him the seventh candidate to make the stage in Los Angeles.

lead_paragraph: CHICAGO — Businessman Andrew Yang qualified Tuesday to participate in next week's Democratic presidential debate, making him the seventh candidate to make the stage in Los Angeles.
